idx.description: A unique identifier for the sample or row in the dataset.

Proteomics_Participant_ID.description: Unique identifier for the participant in the proteomics study.

Case_excluded.description: Indicates whether the participant's case was excluded from the primary analysis.

Proteomics_TMT_batch.description: The batch number for the Tandem Mass Tag (TMT) proteomics experiment.

Proteomics_TMT_plex.description: The plex number within the TMT batch, indicating the number of samples multiplexed in that specific TMT experiment.

Proteomics_TMT_channel.description: The TMT (Tandem Mass Tag) channel used for protein quantification in multiplexed proteomics experiments. Each channel identifies a specific sample.

Proteomics_Parent_Sample_IDs.description: The unique identifier for the parent biospecimen or participant from which the proteomics sample was derived.

Proteomics_Aliquot_ID.description: The unique identifier for a specific aliquot of the proteomics sample.

Proteomics_Tumor_Normal.description: The classification of the proteomics sample origin, indicating whether it is tumor tissue, adjacent normal tissue, or another specific normal tissue type (e.g., myometrium, enriched normal).

Proteomics_OCT.description: Indicates whether the tissue sample was embedded in Optimal Cutting Temperature (OCT) compound for cryopreservation.

Country.description: The country of origin or residence of the patient.

Histologic_Grade_FIGO.description: The histological grade of the tumor according to the FIGO (International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics) grading system.

Myometrial_invasion_Specify.description: The extent of myometrial invasion by the tumor.

Histologic_type.description: The histological type of the tumor.

Treatment_naive.description: Indicates whether the patient has received any prior treatment before the current diagnosis or intervention.

Tumor_purity.description: The estimated purity of the tumor sample, indicating the proportion of tumor cells within the sample.

Path_Stage_Primary_Tumor-pT.description: Pathological T-stage (primary tumor) classifying the size and extent of the primary tumor based on pathological examination, following the TNM/FIGO staging system.

Path_Stage_Reg_Lymph_Nodes-pN.description: Pathological N-stage (regional lymph nodes) classifying the involvement of regional lymph nodes based on pathological examination, following the TNM/FIGO staging system.

Clin_Stage_Dist_Mets-cM.description: Clinical M-stage (distant metastasis) classifying the presence or absence of distant metastases based on clinical examination and imaging, following the TNM staging system.

Path_Stage_Dist_Mets-pM.description: Pathological M-stage (distant metastasis) classifying the presence or absence of distant metastases based on pathological examination, following the TNM staging system.
enum: No pathologic evidence of distant metastasis

tumor_Stage-Pathological.description: Pathological tumor stage, indicating the extent of cancer based on microscopic examination of resected tissue.

FIGO_stage.description: Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging for gynecological cancers, reflecting the extent of the disease.

LVSI.description: Lymphovascular Space Invasion (LVSI), indicating the presence (1) or absence (0) of tumor cells in lymphatic or blood vessels.

BMI.description: Body Mass Index (BMI), a measure of body fat based on height and weight, used to classify weight status.

Age.description: Age of the patient in years.

Diabetes.description: Indicates whether the patient has a history of diabetes.

Race.description: The self-identified racial background of the patient.
enum: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

Ethnicity.description: The self-identified ethnic background of the patient, specifically indicating Hispanic or Latino origin.

Gender.description: The self-identified gender of the patient.

Tumor_Site.description: The anatomical site where the primary tumor is located.

Tumor_Site_Other.description: Describes additional or specific sites of a tumor beyond a primary site, often for cases where the tumor involves multiple or less common anatomical locations.

Tumor_Focality.description: Indicates whether the tumor is present as a single lesion (unifocal) or multiple distinct lesions (multifocal).

Tumor_Size_cm.description: The maximum dimension or size of the tumor, measured in centimeters.

Estrogen_Receptor.description: The status of estrogen receptor expression in tumor cells, indicating whether the cells are positive or negative for the receptor. This is crucial for hormone therapy decisions.

Estrogen_Receptor_%.description: The percentage of tumor cells that stain positive for estrogen receptors. A value of -1.0 might indicate 'not performed' or 'not available' in this context.

Progesterone_Receptor.description: The status of Progesterone Receptor (PR) expression in tumor cells, indicating whether it is positive, negative, or if its status could not be determined.

Progesterone_Receptor_%.description: The percentage of tumor cells that express the Progesterone Receptor (PR), indicating the level of PR positivity. Values typically range from 0 to 100.

MLH1.description: The expression status of the MLH1 protein, a mismatch repair (MMR) protein, often assessed by immunohistochemistry to determine if expression is intact or lost.

MLH2.description: The expression status of the MLH2 protein, a mismatch repair (MMR) protein, often assessed by immunohistochemistry to determine if expression is intact or lost.

MSH6.description: The expression status of the MSH6 protein, a mismatch repair (MMR) protein, often assessed by immunohistochemistry to determine if expression is intact or lost.

PMS2.description: Indicates the immunohistochemical staining status of the PMS2 protein, a key component of the DNA mismatch repair (MMR) system. Loss of expression can suggest Lynch Syndrome or other MMR-deficient tumors.

p53.description: Describes the immunohistochemical staining pattern of the p53 tumor suppressor protein. Abnormal expression (overexpression or loss) is often indicative of TP53 gene mutations and can be associated with aggressive tumor behavior.

Other_IHC_specify.description: A free-text field to specify additional immunohistochemistry (IHC) findings beyond the standard markers, providing details on protein expression patterns of various markers that aid in tumor diagnosis, classification, and prognosis.

MLH1_Promoter_Hypermethylation.description: Indicates the methylation status of the MLH1 gene promoter. Hypermethylation can lead to gene silencing and is a common mechanism for MLH1 deficiency, particularly in sporadic cancers, and can be relevant for Lynch Syndrome diagnosis.

Num_full_term_pregnancies.description: The reported number of full-term pregnancies a patient has experienced. This information is a demographic and medical history variable, potentially relevant for risk assessment in certain diseases.

EPIC_Bcells.description: Estimated proportion or fraction of B cells in a sample, derived using the EPIC (Estimate of Proportions of Immune and Cancer cells) algorithm.

EPIC_CAFs.description: Estimated proportion or fraction of Cancer-Associated Fibroblasts (CAFs) in a sample, derived using the EPIC (Estimate of Proportions of Immune and Cancer cells) algorithm.

EPIC_CD4_Tcells.description: Estimated proportion or fraction of CD4+ T cells (a type of T lymphocyte) in a sample, derived using the EPIC (Estimate of Proportions of Immune and Cancer cells) algorithm.

EPIC_CD8_Tcells.description: Estimated proportion or fraction of CD8+ T cells (a type of T lymphocyte, often cytotoxic) in a sample, derived using the EPIC (Estimate of Proportions of Immune and Cancer cells) algorithm.

EPIC_Endothelial.description: Estimated proportion or fraction of Endothelial cells (cells lining blood vessels) in a sample, derived using the EPIC (Estimate of Proportions of Immune and Cancer cells) algorithm.

EPIC_Macrophages.description: Estimated fraction of Macrophages in the sample, quantified using the EPIC algorithm. Values represent proportions of immune cells in the overall cell population.

EPIC_NKcells.description: Estimated fraction of Natural Killer (NK) cells in the sample, quantified using the EPIC algorithm. Values represent proportions of immune cells in the overall cell population.

EPIC_otherCells.description: Estimated fraction of other uncharacterized cells or non-immune cells in the sample, quantified using the EPIC algorithm. Values represent proportions in the overall cell population.

CIBERSORT_B _cells _naive.description: Estimated fraction of naive B cells in the sample, quantified using the CIBERSORT algorithm. Values represent proportions of immune cells in the overall cell population.

CIBERSORT_B _cells _memory.description: Estimated fraction of memory B cells in the sample, quantified using the CIBERSORT algorithm. Values represent proportions of immune cells in the overall cell population.

CIBERSORT_Plasma _cells.description: The estimated proportion or abundance of plasma cells as derived from CIBERSORT analysis of bulk gene expression data. Values typically range from 0 to 1, representing a fraction of the total cell population.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD8.description: The estimated proportion or abundance of CD8+ T cells as derived from CIBERSORT analysis of bulk gene expression data. Values typically range from 0 to 1, representing a fraction of the total cell population.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _naive.description: The estimated proportion or abundance of naive CD4+ T cells as derived from CIBERSORT analysis of bulk gene expression data. Values typically range from 0 to 1, representing a fraction of the total cell population.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _memory _resting.description: The estimated proportion or abundance of resting memory CD4+ T cells as derived from CIBERSORT analysis of bulk gene expression data. Values typically range from 0 to 1, representing a fraction of the total cell population.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _memory _activat.description: The estimated proportion or abundance of activated memory CD4+ T cells as derived from CIBERSORT analysis of bulk gene expression data. Values typically range from 0 to 1, representing a fraction of the total cell population.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _follicular _helper.description: The estimated proportion of T follicular helper cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _regulatory _(Tregs).description: The estimated proportion of T regulatory cells (Tregs) in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _gamma _delta.description: The estimated proportion of T gamma delta cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution.

CIBERSORT_NK _cells _resting.description: The estimated proportion of resting Natural Killer (NK) cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution.

CIBERSORT_NK _cells _activated.description: The estimated proportion of activated Natural Killer (NK) cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution.

CIBERSORT_Monocytes.description: Estimated abundance of monocytes, derived from CIBERSORT immune cell deconvolution, representing their proportion within a sample.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M0.description: Estimated abundance of M0 (undifferentiated) macrophages, derived from CIBERSORT immune cell deconvolution, representing their proportion within a sample.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M1.description: Estimated abundance of M1 (pro-inflammatory) macrophages, derived from CIBERSORT immune cell deconvolution, representing their proportion within a sample.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M2.description: Estimated abundance of M2 (anti-inflammatory/pro-tumor) macrophages, derived from CIBERSORT immune cell deconvolution, representing their proportion within a sample.

CIBERSORT_Dendritic _cells _resting.description: Estimated abundance of resting dendritic cells, derived from CIBERSORT immune cell deconvolution, representing their proportion within a sample.

CIBERSORT_Dendritic _cells _activated.description: The estimated proportion or score of activated dendritic cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution. Values range from 0 (absent) to 1 (pure population).

CIBERSORT_Mast _cells _resting.description: The estimated proportion or score of resting mast cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution. Values range from 0 (absent) to 1 (pure population).

CIBERSORT_Mast _cells _activated.description: The estimated proportion or score of activated mast cells in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution. Values range from 0 (absent) to 1 (pure population).

CIBERSORT_Eosinophils.description: The estimated proportion or score of eosinophils in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution. Values range from 0 (absent) to 1 (pure population).

CIBERSORT_Neutrophils.description: The estimated proportion or score of neutrophils in a sample, derived using CIBERSORT deconvolution. Values range from 0 (absent) to 1 (pure population).

CIBERSORT_Absolute _score.description: The absolute score derived from CIBERSORT analysis, indicating the relative abundance of specific immune cell types within a mixed cell population.

ESTIMATE_StromalScore.description: The stromal score calculated using the ESTIMATE algorithm, reflecting the presence of stromal cells in the tumor microenvironment.

ESTIMATE_ImmuneScore.description: The immune score calculated using the ESTIMATE algorithm, reflecting the presence of immune cells in the tumor microenvironment.

ESTIMATE_ESTIMATEScore.description: The overall ESTIMATE score, which is the sum of the stromal and immune scores, providing an aggregate measure of non-tumor cell infiltration in the tumor microenvironment.

Stemness_score.description: A quantitative score indicating the degree of stemness, or similarity to embryonic stem cells, derived from gene expression profiles or other genomic data.

ER_ESR1.description: Expression level or activity of Estrogen Receptor 1 (ESR1), a nuclear receptor involved in estrogen signaling, often relevant in breast cancer.

PR_PGR.description: Expression level or activity of Progesterone Receptor (PGR), another nuclear receptor involved in progesterone signaling, often relevant in breast cancer.

Pathway_activity_EGFR.description: Activity score or level of the Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor (EGFR) signaling pathway, crucial for cell growth, proliferation, and survival.

Pathway_activity_Hypoxia.description: Activity score or level of the Hypoxia pathway, representing the cellular response to low oxygen conditions.

Pathway_activity_JAK.STAT.description: Activity score or level of the JAK-STAT signaling pathway, a key mediator of cytokine and growth factor signaling, involved in immune response and cell growth.

Pathway_activity_MAPK.description: Represents the activity score or level of the Mitogen-Activated Protein Kinase (MAPK) signaling pathway, often inferred from omics data. Values typically indicate a relative measure of pathway activation.

Pathway_activity_NFkB.description: Represents the activity score or level of the Nuclear Factor Kappa B (NFkB) signaling pathway, often inferred from omics data. Values typically indicate a relative measure of pathway activation.

Pathway_activity_PI3K.description: Represents the activity score or level of the Phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) signaling pathway, often inferred from omics data. Values typically indicate a relative measure of pathway activation.

Pathway_activity_TGFb.description: Represents the activity score or level of the Transforming Growth Factor-beta (TGFb) signaling pathway, often inferred from omics data. Values typically indicate a relative measure of pathway activation.

Pathway_activity_TNFa.description: Represents the activity score or level of the Tumor Necrosis Factor-alpha (TNFa) signaling pathway, often inferred from omics data. Values typically indicate a relative measure of pathway activation.

Pathway_activity_Trail.description: Quantified activity score representing the activity level of the TRAIL (TNF-related apoptosis-inducing ligand) signaling pathway. Higher absolute values indicate stronger pathway modulation.

Pathway_activity_VEGF.description: Quantified activity score representing the activity level of the VEGF (Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor) signaling pathway. Higher absolute values indicate stronger pathway modulation.

Pathway_activity_p53.description: Quantified activity score representing the activity level of the p53 tumor suppressor pathway. Higher absolute values indicate stronger pathway modulation.

TP53_ATM.description: Binary indicator for a specific molecular interaction or alteration between the TP53 and ATM genes or their associated pathways. 1 indicates presence, 0 indicates absence.

TP53_CHEK2.description: Binary indicator for a specific molecular interaction or alteration between the TP53 and CHEK2 genes or their associated pathways. 1 indicates presence, 0 indicates absence.

TP53_MDM4.description: Indicates the activity or status of the interaction between TP53 and MDM4 within a pathway context, often representing a binary state where 0 signifies inactive/wild-type and 1 signifies active/mutated/altered.

TP53_RPS6KA3.description: Indicates the activity or status of the interaction between TP53 and RPS6KA3 (also known as p90RSK) within a pathway context, often representing a binary state where 0 signifies inactive/wild-type and 1 signifies active/mutated/altered.

TP53_TP53.description: Indicates the overall activity or status of the TP53 gene itself within a pathway context, often representing a binary state where 0 signifies inactive/wild-type and 1 signifies active/mutated/altered.

TP53_pathway.description: Indicates the overall activity or status of the TP53 signaling pathway, often representing a binary state where 0 signifies inactive and 1 signifies active or altered pathway status.

PI3K_AKT1.description: Indicates the activity or status of the interaction between PI3K and AKT1, key components of the PI3K/AKT pathway, often representing a binary state where 0 signifies inactive/wild-type and 1 signifies active/mutated/altered.

PI3K_AKT2.description: Binary indicator for the presence or activity of the AKT2 protein within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates presence/activity, and 0.0 indicates absence/inactivity.

PI3K_AKT3.description: Binary indicator for the presence or activity of the AKT3 protein within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates presence/activity, and 0.0 indicates absence/inactivity.

PI3K_DEPDC5.description: Binary indicator for the presence or activity of the DEPDC5 protein within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates presence/activity, and 0.0 indicates absence/inactivity.

PI3K_DEPTOR.description: Binary indicator for the presence or activity of the DEPTOR protein within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates presence/activity, and 0.0 indicates absence/inactivity.

PI3K_INPP4B.description: Binary indicator for the presence or activity of the INPP4B protein within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates presence/activity, and 0.0 indicates absence/inactivity.

PI3K_MAPKAP1.description: Indicates the status or expression level of MAPKAP1, a component of the PI3K pathway. A value of 1.0 typically denotes presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity. Missing values (NaN) suggest data unavailability.

PI3K_MLST8.description: Indicates the status or expression level of MLST8, a component of the PI3K pathway. A value of 1.0 typically denotes presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity. Missing values (NaN) suggest data unavailability.

PI3K_MTOR.description: Indicates the status or expression level of MTOR, a central component of the PI3K pathway. A value of 1.0 typically denotes presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity. Missing values (NaN) suggest data unavailability.

PI3K_NPRL2.description: Indicates the status or expression level of NPRL2, a component of the PI3K pathway. A value of 1.0 typically denotes presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity. Missing values (NaN) suggest data unavailability.

PI3K_NPRL3.description: Indicates the status or expression level of NPRL3, a component of the PI3K pathway. A value of 1.0 typically denotes presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity. Missing values (NaN) suggest data unavailability.

PI3K_PDK1.description: A binary indicator representing the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or specific event) of the Phosphoinositide-dependent kinase 1 (PDK1) component within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 typically indicates presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity.

PI3K_PIK3CA.description: A binary indicator representing the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or specific event) of the Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate 3-kinase catalytic subunit alpha (PIK3CA) component within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 typically indicates presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity.

PI3K_PIK3CB.description: A binary indicator representing the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or specific event) of the Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate 3-kinase catalytic subunit beta (PIK3CB) component within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 typically indicates presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity.

PI3K_PIK3R1.description: A binary indicator representing the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or specific event) of the Phosphoinositide-3-kinase regulatory subunit 1 (PIK3R1) component within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 typically indicates presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity.

PI3K_PIK3R2.description: A binary indicator representing the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or specific event) of the Phosphoinositide-3-kinase regulatory subunit 2 (PIK3R2) component within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 typically indicates presence or activation, while 0.0 indicates absence or inactivity.

PI3K_PPP2R1A.description: Indicates the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or presence) of PPP2R1A, a regulatory subunit of protein phosphatase 2A, within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_PTEN.description: Indicates the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or presence) of PTEN (Phosphatase and Tensin Homolog), a key tumor suppressor gene that negatively regulates the PI3K/AKT pathway.

PI3K_RHEB.description: Indicates the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or presence) of RHEB (Ras Homolog Enriched in Brain), a small GTPase that activates mTORC1, within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_RICTOR.description: Indicates the status (e.g., activation, mutation, or presence) of RICTOR (Rapamycin-Insensitive Companion of mTOR), a component of mTORC2, within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_RPS6.description: Indicates the status (e.g., phosphorylation, activation, or presence) of RPS6 (Ribosomal Protein S6), a downstream target of mTOR signaling, within the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_RPS6KB1.description: Indicates the activity or status of RPS6KB1 (ribosomal protein S6 kinase B1) within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1 typically represents activation or a specific state, while 0 represents inactivity or an alternative state.

PI3K_RPTOR.description: Represents the activity or status of RPTOR (regulatory-associated protein of mTOR) in the context of the PI3K pathway, often indicating the state of the mTORC1 complex. A value of 1 typically represents activation or a specific state, while 0 represents inactivity or an alternative state.

PI3K_STK11.description: Indicates the activity or status of STK11 (serine/threonine kinase 11, also known as LKB1) related to the PI3K signaling pathway, often involved in regulating mTOR and AMPK. A value of 1 typically represents activation or a specific state, while 0 represents inactivity or an alternative state.

PI3K_TSC1.description: Represents the activity or status of TSC1 (Tuberous Sclerosis Complex 1), a component of the TSC complex that negatively regulates mTOR within the PI3K pathway. A value of 1 typically represents activation or a specific state, while 0 represents inactivity or an alternative state.

PI3K_TSC2.description: Indicates the activity or status of TSC2 (Tuberous Sclerosis Complex 2), another component of the TSC complex that negatively regulates mTOR within the PI3K pathway. A value of 1 typically represents activation or a specific state, while 0 represents inactivity or an alternative state.

PI3K_pathway.description: Indicates the activity or status of the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 typically signifies activation or presence, while 0.0 signifies inactivity or absence.

HRD_BRCA1.description: Indicates the presence or absence of Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) specifically associated with the BRCA1 gene. A value of 1.0 indicates HRD, and 0.0 indicates no HRD.

HRD_BRCA2.description: Indicates the presence or absence of Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) specifically associated with the BRCA2 gene. A value of 1.0 indicates HRD, and 0.0 indicates no HRD.

HRD_BRCA1_or_BRCA2.description: Indicates the presence or absence of Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) associated with either the BRCA1 or BRCA2 gene. A value of 1.0 indicates HRD, and 0.0 indicates no HRD.

CNV_DEL.description: Represents a quantitative score or frequency for Copy Number Variation deletion events. Higher values indicate a greater extent or significance of deletions.

CNV_AMP.description: Represents the amplification level or score of a Copy Number Variation (CNV). Higher values indicate greater amplification.

CNV_class.description: Categorical classification of the Copy Number Variation (CNV) status or level.

CNV_idx.description: An index or score indicating the overall burden or significance of Copy Number Variation (CNV).

CNV_1q_DEL.description: Represents the deletion level or score for Copy Number Variation (CNV) specifically on chromosome arm 1q. Negative values indicate deletion.

CNV_3q_DEL.description: Represents the deletion level or score for Copy Number Variation (CNV) specifically on chromosome arm 3q. Negative values indicate deletion.

CNV_4q_DEL.description: A continuous numerical value representing the copy number variation status of chromosome 4q, specifically indicating deletions (DEL). Lower (more negative) values suggest a stronger deletion event, while values closer to zero indicate no or minimal deletion.

CNV_1q_AMP.description: A continuous numerical value representing the copy number variation status of chromosome 1q, specifically indicating an amplification (AMP). Higher values suggest a stronger amplification event, while values closer to zero indicate no or minimal amplification.

CNV_3q_AMP.description: A continuous numerical value representing the copy number variation status of chromosome 3q, specifically indicating an amplification (AMP). Higher values suggest a stronger amplification event, while values closer to zero indicate no or minimal amplification.

CNV_4q_AMP.description: A continuous numerical value representing the copy number variation status of chromosome 4q, specifically indicating an amplification (AMP). Higher values suggest a stronger amplification event, while values closer to zero indicate no or minimal amplification.

Purity_Immune.description: A continuous numerical value representing the estimated purity or fraction of immune cells within a sample. Values typically range between 0 and 1, where 1 indicates 100% immune cell purity.

Purity_Cancer.description: Represents the estimated proportion of cancer cells within a tumor sample. Tumor purity is a critical factor influencing downstream genomic and transcriptomic interpretations, typically ranging from 0 to 1.

Purity_Stroma.description: Represents the estimated proportion of stromal cells (non-cancerous connective tissue) within a tumor sample. Stromal content can influence tumor microenvironment studies and treatment response, typically ranging from 0 to 1.

MSI_status.description: Microsatellite Instability (MSI) status indicates the presence of mutations in short, repetitive DNA sequences (microsatellites). It is a biomarker for certain cancers, particularly colorectal cancer, and can predict response to immunotherapy.

POLE_subtype.description: POLE (DNA Polymerase Epsilon) subtype refers to the presence or absence of mutations in the POLE gene. POLE mutations are associated with ultra-mutated tumors and often a favorable prognosis in certain cancer types.

JAK1_MS_INDEL.description: Indicates the status of JAK1 (Janus Kinase 1) gene mutations, specifically microsatellite indels (insertions/deletions). JAK1 mutations can impact immune signaling and are relevant in cancer immunology and resistance to therapy.

JAK1_Mutation.description: The mutation status or specific type of mutation observed in the Janus kinase 1 (JAK1) gene.

Log2_variant_per_Mbp.description: The log2 transformed count of all genetic variants (including SNPs and INDELs) per megabase pair (Mbp) of sequenced DNA. This metric often reflects the overall variant density or tumor mutation burden (TMB).

Log2_SNP_per_Mbp.description: The log2 transformed count of single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) per megabase pair (Mbp) of sequenced DNA.

Log2_INDEL_per_Mbp.description: The log2 transformed count of insertions and deletions (INDELs) per megabase pair (Mbp) of sequenced DNA.

Log2_variant_total.description: The log2 transformed total count of all genetic variants (including SNPs and INDELs) detected across the entire sequenced region or genome.

Log2_SNP_total.description: The base-2 logarithm of the total number of Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms (SNPs) detected in the genomic sample.

Log2_INDEL_total.description: The base-2 logarithm of the total number of Insertions and Deletions (INDELs) detected in the genomic sample.

Genomics_subtype.description: The classification of the genomic subtype for the sample, indicating distinct genomic characteristics such as microsatellite instability or copy number variation status.

Mutation_signature_C>A.description: The normalized contribution or frequency of the C>A (Cytosine to Adenine) mutation signature, representing a specific pattern of DNA damage and repair in the genome.

Mutation_signature_C>G.description: The normalized contribution or frequency of the C>G (Cytosine to Guanine) mutation signature, representing a specific pattern of DNA damage and repair in the genome.

Mutation_signature_C>T.description: The percentage or normalized count of C>T mutations in a sample's trinucleotide mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>C.description: The percentage or normalized count of T>C mutations in a sample's trinucleotide mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>A.description: The percentage or normalized count of T>A mutations in a sample's trinucleotide mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>G.description: The percentage or normalized count of T>G mutations in a sample's trinucleotide mutation signature.

WXS_normal_sample_type.description: The type of normal sample used for Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) as a reference or control.

WXS_normal_filename.description: The filename for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) normal sample.

WXS_normal_UUID.description: The Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) normal sample.

WXS_tumor_sample_type.description: The sample type for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) tumor sample.

WXS_tumor_filename.description: The filename for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) tumor sample.

WXS_tumor_UUID.description: The Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) tumor sample.

WGS_normal_sample_type.description: The type of the normal sample used for Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS), indicating its origin or characteristics.

WGS_normal_UUID.description: The Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the normal sample used in Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS), linking to its data.

WGS_tumor_sample_type.description: The type of the tumor sample used for Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS), indicating its origin or characteristics.

WGS_tumor_UUID.description: The Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the tumor sample used in Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS), linking to its data.

RNAseq_R1_sample_type.description: The type of sample used for the first replicate (R1) of RNA sequencing, indicating its origin or characteristics.

RNAseq_R1_filename.description: The filename for the first read (R1) of an RNA sequencing experiment, typically in FASTQ.gz format.

RNAseq_R1_UUID.description: The Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) assigned to the file containing the first read (R1) of an RNA sequencing experiment.

RNAseq_R2_sample_type.description: The biological sample type from which the RNA sequencing data (second read, R2) was derived.

RNAseq_R2_filename.description: The filename for the second read (R2) of an RNA sequencing experiment, typically in FASTQ.gz format.

RNAseq_R2_UUID.description: The Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) assigned to the file containing the second read (R2) of an RNA sequencing experiment.

miRNAseq_sample_type.description: The type of biological sample from which the miRNA sequencing data was derived.

miRNAseq_UUID.description: A universally unique identifier (UUID) for the miRNA sequencing sample.

Methylation_available.description: Indicates whether methylation data is available for the corresponding sample.

Methylation_quality.description: The quality assessment status of the methylation data.
